MODISoptions            Set or retrieve permanent MODIS package options
arcStats                Get summarisation of local MODIS hdf data. As
                        Plot or as Table.
delHdf                  Delete MODIS grid files to reduce the local
                        storage
detectBitInfo           List MODIS QA (Quality) SDS information:
                        bitShift and bitMask
extractDate             Extract dates from (MODIS) files
file.size               Size in Byte of file(s)
genTile                 Generate tiling system
getCollection           Get available collections of MODIS product(s)
getHdf                  Create or update a local, user-defined subset
                        of the global online MODIS grid data pool.
getProduct              Check the avalability of a given product,
                        create file related information
getSds                  List SDS in a MODIS grid file
getTile                 Get MODIS tile id(s)
makeWeights             Extract bit-encoded information from a raster
                        file. Create a weihgts rasterfile
orgStruc                Re-organise MODIS files in the local data
                        archive
orgTime                 Handles the in/output date used in the
                        filerting
preStack                Organises (MODIS) files for the generation of a
                        RasterStack object
repDoy                  'Repair' DOY values in MODIS composites:
                        'composite_day_of_the_year' layer/SDS
runGdal                 Process MODIS hdf with GDAL
runMrt                  Run Modis Reprojection Tool ('MRT-grid') with
                        specified parameters
search4map              Function for 'mapdata' dearch
smooth.spline.raster    Filter time series imagery with a cubic spline
transDate               Function for MODIS date conversions and
                        testing.
whittaker.raster        Filter vegetation index time series imagery
                        with the modified whittaker approach
